name: {{ .Name }}
version: 0.1.0
categories:
  - Misc
author: Unknown
{{- if eq .FilterType "network" }}
description: A custom Rust network (L4) extension.
longDescription: |
  A custom Rust network filter built with Envoy's dynamic module framework.

  ## Features

  * **Connection logging**: Logs a tag on every new TCP connection
  * **Configurable**: Configure the log tag via JSON config

  ## Configuration

  Configure the extension with a JSON object:
  - `log_tag`: The tag to log on new connections (default: "example")

  ## Building

  This is a Rust dynamic module that must be compiled to a shared library.

  ```bash
  cargo build --release
  ```

  The compiled library will be at `target/release/lib{{ .LibName }}.{so,dylib}`
tags:
  - rust
  - dynamic-module
  - network
  - filter
license: Apache-2.0
type: rust
filterType: network
examples:
  - title: Basic Usage
    description: Run the extension with default configuration
    code: |
      boe run --extension {{ .Name }}
  - title: Custom Log Tag
    description: Configure a custom log tag
    code: |
      boe run --extension {{ .Name }} --config '
        {
          "log_tag": "my-custom-tag"
        }'
{{- else }}
description: A custom Rust extension.
longDescription: |
  A custom Rust extension built with Envoy's dynamic module framework.

  ## Features

  * **Custom Header**: Adds a custom header to requests and responses
  * **Configurable**: Configure the header value via JSON config

  ## Configuration

  Configure the extension with a JSON object:
  - `header_value`: The value to set in the custom header (default: "example")

  ## Building

  This is a Rust dynamic module that must be compiled to a shared library.

  ```bash
  cargo build --release
  ```

  The compiled library will be at `target/release/lib{{ .LibName }}.{so,dylib}`
tags:
  - rust
  - dynamic-module
  - http
  - filter
license: Apache-2.0
type: rust
examples:
  - title: Basic Usage
    description: Run the extension with default configuration
    code: |
      boe run --extension {{ .Name }}
  - title: Custom Header Value
    description: Configure a custom header value
    code: |
      boe run --extension {{ .Name }} --config '
        {
          "header_value": "my-custom-value"
        }'
{{- end }}
